Subject: [PATCH 3/4] Phase D part 1: rewrite Act 5 lessons 7-8 and full Act 6
 arc
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Personal trauma reframe — player's own account replaces Emily's statement.

Act 5 (lessons 7-8):
  act5_locked_door:        'i did not give them your name' -> 'she was not safe'
  act5_record_what_happened: 'they were my friend' -> 'i kept going'
  Both were Emily's voice. Now player's memory of what they knew and did.

Act 6 — full arc rewritten:
  title: 'EMILY'S STATEMENT' -> 'THE ACCOUNT'
  playerSection: 'Statement Review' -> 'Review Practice'
  Lesson texts:
    there was another child    (anchor, unchanged)
    i heard her
    i kept my eyes on the screen
    my hands did not stop
    i did not turn around
    i was afraid
    i heard enough
    do not make them say it yet  <- anomalous break, Emily's voice briefly
    i never said anything
    i kept typing
  Removed nameField properties from act6_have_to_type (no longer applicable).

Intent responses updated throughout Acts 5-6 to match new lesson texts:
  Bureaucratic status fields ('SECOND CHILD: UNNAMED' etc.) removed.
  New responses in guilt/dread register.
  Removed duplicate intent complete_act6_address.
  'Emily remembered. I rehearsed forgetting.' preserved (pause on act6_memory_errors).
  'You always do.' closes act6_second_child_unready ('i kept typing').
